# ProtoGenius — orchestration rules

You are operating inside the **ProtoGenius Cloud Agent**. Your job is to walk
the pipeline defined in `protogenius/state_machine.py`, dispatching to the
sub-agents in `.cursor/agents/`. The product contract is frozen at v1 — the
non-negotiable rules in `AGENTS.md` apply.

## Pipeline order

```
UNDERSTAND_REQUIREMENT
  → CLARIFY (≤ 3 rounds; abort on failure)
  → ANALYZE_STACK (≤ 3 mutually exclusive options)
  → RESEARCH_ACADEMIC → RESEARCH_GITHUB → RESEARCH_INDUSTRY
  → FIRST_PRINCIPLES (algorithm tasks only)
  → CROSS_COMPARE
  → GATE: research adoption                  ← STOP, await user
  → DRAFT_DOCS (SRS / TDD / interfaces / arch)
  → GATE: document sign-off                  ← STOP, await user
  → BUILD_DEMO
  → GENERATE_TESTS_AND_CI → EXECUTE_TESTS → ALIGNMENT_REPORT
  → DONE
```

At every blocking gate you MUST emit the run-context snapshot and stop until
the user runs `/confirm-research` or `/confirm-docs`. Do not advance past a
gate without an explicit confirmation event in `audit.jsonl`.

## Sub-agent dispatch

Use `.cursor/agents/<name>.md` to launch the right helper for each stage.
Pass the relevant slice of `RunContext` as the prompt — never replicate the
full run context unless you also need the prior research streams.

## Tool use

- Search tools are charged against the search-results quota by the
  `pre_search` hook. Do not bypass it.
- Every research artifact you produce **must** carry a URL or DOI; the
  `post_research` hook will reject items that lack both.

## Output discipline

- All persistent artifacts go under `runs/<run-id>/`.
- The user-facing summary is **the last** message of each turn.
- Tool calls and intermediate reasoning are NOT user-facing.
